{
  "page": "Coronation of Aegon II Targaryen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:AEGON_II.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/46/AEGON_II.jpg/300px-AEGON_II.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"420\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/46/AEGON_II.jpg/450px-AEGON_II.jpg 1.5x, /images/4/46/AEGON_II.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:AEGON_II.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a>, by Amok ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>coronation of Aegon II Targaryen</b> occurred in <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a> near the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Coronation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Coronation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Attendees\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attendees</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Royal_House\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Royal House</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Royal_Household\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Royal Household</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I Targaryen</a> chose Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, his daughter by his first queen, <a href=\"/index.php/Aemma_Arryn\" title=\"Aemma Arryn\">Aemma Arryn</a>, as his preferred heir over Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, the king's eldest son by his second queen, <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> After Viserys died in his sleep within the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a>, Alicent concealed the king's death from the public and gathered support in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> for her son, Aegon the Elder, against the claim of Rhaenyra, who was pregnant at <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. After the death of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lyman_Beesbury\" title=\"Lyman Beesbury\">Lyman Beesbury</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> began making plans for Aegon's coronation. According to Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Eustace (Dance of the Dragons)\">Eustace</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Kingsguard\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Kingsguard\">Lord Commander of the Kingsguard</a>, convinced a reluctant Prince Aegon to accept the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a> because his mother, brothers, sister and children would otherwise be killed by Rhaenyra.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Aegon chose to don <a href=\"/index.php/Crown#Crown_of_Aegon_I\" title=\"Crown\">the crown</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> for his reign. Alicent, the dowager queen, ordered that <a href=\"/index.php/Crown#Crown_of_Jaehaerys_I\" title=\"Crown\">Viserys's crown</a> be locked away, but the steward carrying it disappeared instead. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Steffon_Darklyn\" title=\"Steffon Darklyn\">Steffon Darklyn</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>, choosing Rhaenyra over Aegon, fled to Dragonstone to give Rhaenyra the crown of her father.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Coronation\">Coronation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Coronation\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Aegon II's hastily-arranged coronation was held in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonpit\" title=\"Dragonpit\">Dragonpit</a> because of its seating capacity and defensibility. Ser Criston placed Aegon the Conqueror's crown on the new monarch's brow and proclaimed him <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Andals,_the_Rhoynar,_and_the_First_Men\" title=\"King of the Andals, the Rhoynar, and the First Men\">King of the Andals, the Rhoynar, and the First Men</a>. Alicent then placed her own crown atop <a href=\"/index.php/Helaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Helaena Targaryen\">Helaena Targaryen</a>, Aegon's sister-wife. Septon Eustace anointed Aegon's brow with holy oils and blessed him in the names of <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">the Seven</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Munkun\" title=\"Munkun\">Munkun</a> wrote about Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a>'s claim that more than a hundred thousand <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> were in attendance, with their cheers shaking the walls of the Dragonpit. Rhaenyra's fool <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a>, however, wrote that the benches were only half full.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After his coronation, Aegon flew on his <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a>, three times around King's Landing before landing in the Red Keep. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arryk_Cargyll\" title=\"Arryk Cargyll\">Arryk Cargyll</a> of the Kingsguard escorted the new king to the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Hall_(Red_Keep)\" title=\"Great Hall (Red Keep)\">throne room</a>, where he sat the Iron Throne before a thousand <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Knights\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Knights\">knights</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After bringing forth a stillborn, deformed girl she named <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Visenya</a>, Rhaenyra had <a href=\"/index.php/Coronation_of_Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Coronation of Rhaenyra Targaryen\">her own coronation</a> at Dragonstone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attendees\">Attendees</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Attendees\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Royal_House\">Royal House</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Royal House\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Helaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Helaena Targaryen\">Helaena Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Hightower\" title=\"House Hightower\"><img alt=\"House Hightower.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/House_Hightower.svg/20px-House_Hightower.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/House_Hightower.svg/30px-House_Hightower.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fe/House_Hightower.svg/40px-House_Hightower.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Dowager Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Royal_Household\">Royal Household</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Royal Household\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/20px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/30px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/40px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/20px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/30px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/40px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arryk_Cargyll\" title=\"Arryk Cargyll\">Arryk Cargyll</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/20px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/30px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/40px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Willis_Fell\" title=\"Willis Fell\">Willis Fell</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/20px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/30px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/40px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rickard_Thorne\" title=\"Rickard Thorne\">Rickard Thorne</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Maesters\" title=\"Maesters\"><img alt=\"Maester.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/20px-Maester.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/30px-Maester.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/46/Maester.svg/40px-Maester.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\"><img alt=\"Star of the Faith.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/20px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/30px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/40px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Eustace (Dance of the Dragons)\">Eustace</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Coronation_of_Aegon_II_Targaryen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=